(firstQuint)Study of Resiniferatoxin for Knee Pain in Moderate to Severe Osteoarthritis.

 This study is to evaluate the safety of resiniferatoxin administered intra-articularly to subjects with moderate or severe knee pain due to osteoarthritis (OA).

 It is also to assess the preliminary efficacy of resiniferatoxin to relieve knee pain when walking.

